<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-430-685  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 430 685.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  Sept 17 1990 n318 p2(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Redundancy plan: users applaud N.Y. Telephone move. (plan to filetariff for fiber optic connections)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Schwartz, Jeffrey.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>New York Telephone Co. pleases its customers by announcing atariff to provide redundant fiber optic services that willalleviate the problems caused by power failures.andP;  Fiber installedin customers' buildings will connect them to two of the telephonecompany's central offices.andP;  The company's initial disasterprevention efforts will concern T1 and DS-3 lines and areparticularly appreciated by large financial services providers.andO;New fiber installations will mean a 15 percent increase on thecost of a line.andP;  Tariffs next year will improve central officeredundancy for switched services, allowing users to split theirincoming calls between two central office exchanges so if one goesdown they can continue to operate.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   New York Telephone Co. (services).andO;Topic:     RedundancyFiber OpticsNew YorkPower FailureDisaster RecoveryFinancial ServicesTelecommunications Services.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>